cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the internal workings of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and how they learn to look at images. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm to backtrack the important pixels considered by the CNN, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as well. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
